# Git Auth Safety

- Never read `.env`, `.env.local`, or any secrets file to obtain git credentials.
- Never source env files for `git push`, `git fetch`, or other git auth operations.
- Prefer normal credentialed git commands (credential helper, keychain, or existing logged-in session).
- If git auth is missing, ask the user to run push locally or provide a secure auth path instead of reading local secret files.

## Allowed Pattern

- Run `git push origin main` directly.
- If it fails with auth errors, stop and ask for the preferred auth method.
